claim.claim-text:
1. A process for preparing polymorphic olanzapine Form I comprising:
a) reacting 4-amino-2-methyl-10H-thieno[2,3-b][1,5]benzodiazepine HCI and 1-methylpiperazine in an aprotic high boiling solvent or mixtures thereof at a temperature of between about 90° C. to 130° C.;
b) purifying the product of step a) in an acidic medium;
c) basifying the product of step b) to a pH of between 7.5-9; and
d) extracting the product of step c) using a low boiling organic solvent.
